{"article_id":"AtQBPSFeSvSAkQuz","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"A group","depth":8},{"id":1,"text":"called AllSides","depth":8},{"id":2,"text":"put out a report Tuesday","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"which concludes","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"that Google News ' search results are biased toward the left end of the political spectrum .","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"However , the report also states","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"that this bias seems to reflect the general bias of sites","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"which are popular on the web","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"and doesn ' t represent evidence","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"that Google is intentionally skewing results .","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"In other words , Google ' s results are biased","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"but they aren ' t rigged .","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"From USA Today :","depth":5},{"id":13,"text":"John Gable , CEO of AllSides and author of the study , said","depth":6},{"id":14,"text":"the bias is the result of \" most news online and most news consumption online","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"( being ) from a left perspective. \"","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"AllSides specializes in identifying media bias for the purpose","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"of providing balanced perspectives .","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"The group uses a media bias ratings","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"based on popular opinion","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"to rank media outlets as either left , right or center .","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"\" If you look at where people get news online","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"and you rate it ,","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"most of it is coming from the left , \"","depth":7},{"id":24,"text":"Gable said .","depth":6},{"id":25,"text":"He said","depth":6},{"id":26,"text":"Google search results come from what is largely a \" popularity algorithm , \"","depth":7},{"id":27,"text":"meaning that viewpoints","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"more people have","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"are more likely to be highlighted .","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"As a result , viewpoints","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"that are outside the majority","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"don ' t appear as high up in search results...","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"\" If their role is just to reflect the internet ,","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"they ' re doing a fine job , \"","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"he said .","depth":7},{"id":36,"text":"\" ... If they think","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"their job is to empower people to decide for themselves ,","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"they actually need to make a change . \"","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"So how does AllSides determine","depth":4},{"id":40,"text":"which news sources are left and right ?","depth":4},{"id":41,"text":"The answer is that they don ' t .","depth":5},{"id":42,"text":"As you can see on this page ,","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"the group asks people to rate their own bias","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"( left or right )","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"and then asks them to rate the bias of articles from various sites","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"and averages how different groups","depth":12},{"id":47,"text":"( left , right , and center )","depth":12},{"id":48,"text":"respond to various articles .","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"The result is a master list","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"which rates various news sites from far left","depth":12},{"id":51,"text":"( HuffPost )","depth":12},{"id":52,"text":"to far right","depth":12},{"id":53,"text":"( Breitbart ) .","depth":12},{"id":54,"text":"Some sites fall in the center","depth":11},{"id":55,"text":"( CNBC )","depth":11},{"id":56,"text":"while others lean left","depth":12},{"id":57,"text":"( Buzzfeed )","depth":12},{"id":58,"text":"or lean right","depth":12},{"id":59,"text":"( Hot Air ) .","depth":12},{"id":60,"text":"Here ' s a chart from the report","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"showing a sample of results :","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"You can , of course , take issue with any of the conclusions in that graphic or the master list","depth":8},{"id":63,"text":"it is based on","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"but the idea is that people on all sides are having a say about the spectrum .","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"It ' s not the opinion of one person or a small group of people .","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"So","depth":9},{"id":67,"text":"starting from that foundation ,","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"the site looked at Google ' s search results","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"and found this :","depth":8},{"id":70,"text":"This study completed 123 different measurements of the political bias of Google News and Google News search results over 14 days from August 23 to September 5 , 2018 .","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"This produced three summary views of the political bias of Google News...","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"The aggregate result indicates","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"that the overall bias of Google News is 65 % left , 20 % center , 16 % right .","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"Because the majority of traffic goes to the very first links","depth":12},{"id":75,"text":"displayed on Google ,","depth":12},{"id":76,"text":"with an estimated one-third going to the first result ,","depth":11},{"id":77,"text":"the position of a link on a page is extremely important .","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"While our overall analysis takes this into account","depth":13},{"id":79,"text":"by measuring the bias of just the top 5 results separately from the rest of the first page ,","depth":13},{"id":80,"text":"it is also important to consider where the first result from a left , center or right source appears .","depth":12},{"id":81,"text":"Being in the very first position is extremely impactful .","depth":11},{"id":82,"text":"Here is the average position of the first result from the left , center or right :","depth":11},{"id":83,"text":"- Left :","depth":13},{"id":84,"text":"average 1.7","depth":14},{"id":85,"text":"( one of the top 2 results )","depth":14},{"id":86,"text":"- Center :","depth":14},{"id":87,"text":"5.3","depth":15},{"id":88,"text":"( averages","depth":16},{"id":89,"text":"to be in the top 5 or 6 results )","depth":16},{"id":90,"text":"- Right :","depth":15},{"id":91,"text":"12.2","depth":15},{"id":92,"text":"( this is below \" the fold \"","depth":15},{"id":93,"text":"meaning that users have to scroll down the window on their computer screen","depth":16},{"id":94,"text":"before they see their first news article from the right )","depth":16},{"id":95,"text":"These results","depth":11},{"id":96,"text":"that show a strong bias for left media over right media","depth":11},{"id":97,"text":"are also consistent with past research and observations by AllSides .","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"AllSides analyzes the news on a daily basis","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"and have often found it difficult to find perspectives from the right","depth":11},{"id":100,"text":"when using Google News...","depth":11},{"id":101,"text":"This apparent bias could easily be the natural and unintended consequence of its algorithms and the fact","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"that most news outlets , as well as most journalists , have political views","depth":10},{"id":103,"text":"that represent the left side of the US political spectrum .","depth":10},{"id":104,"text":"Online news consumers are younger and lean farther Left than the average American ,","depth":8},{"id":105,"text":"and that directly impacts which articles Google ' s algorithm selects","depth":9},{"id":106,"text":"and how high it places them on the page .","depth":9},{"id":107,"text":"This study does not suggest","depth":9},{"id":108,"text":"that there is intentional favoritism for media sources from the left ,","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"nor does this study suggest the opposite .","depth":8},{"id":110,"text":"It only demonstrates","depth":9},{"id":111,"text":"that the resulting choice of links","depth":11},{"id":112,"text":"that Google News provides","depth":11},{"id":113,"text":"do have a significant bias in favor of the left .","depth":10},{"id":114,"text":"So there is strong evidence","depth":10},{"id":115,"text":"that Google ' s search results favor left-wing news sources","depth":10},{"id":116,"text":"but this may be because that ' s what online news readers are looking at the most on their own .","depth":9},{"id":117,"text":"To put it another way ,","depth":7},{"id":118,"text":"Google may be reflecting a bias","depth":8},{"id":119,"text":"rather than directing one .","depth":8},{"id":120,"text":"The full report with a lot more detail on the methodology and findings is 39-pages long","depth":2},{"id":121,"text":"and can be found here .","depth":2}],"relations":[{"parent":243,"left":241,"right":242,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":241,"left":160,"right":240,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":160,"left":137,"right":159,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":137,"left":133,"right":136,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":133,"left":126,"right":132,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":126,"left":124,"right":125,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":124,"left":123,"right":2,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":123,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":125,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":132,"left":130,"right":131,"relation":"restatement","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":130,"left":5,"right":129,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":129,"left":127,"right":128,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":127,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":128,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":131,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":136,"left":12,"right":135,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":135,"left":13,"right":134,"